  "text": "Animals were euthanized in an unstressed basal state on post-natal day 40, as previously reported [CITATION_1] , and both left and right hippocampi were removed and frozen immediately on dry ice. To analyze gene expression and DNA methylation from these tissues, genomic DNA and RNA were extracted simultaneously from 20 mg of powdered right hippocampus using the AllPrep DNA/RNA/miRNA Universal Kit (Qiagen, Ontario, Canada). In the present study, the hippocampi from female juvenile offspring (n = 5-7/gp; F 1 , F 2 , F 3 vehicle; F 1 , F 2 , F 3 sGC) were used for molecular analysis. Our previous studies had indicated that juvenile females showed the greatest differences in behavioural and neuroendocrine phenotypes (pituitary-adrenal function and open-filed activity) associated with prenatal sGC exposure [CITATION_2] . All female offspring used in this study were derived from independent mothers, and each mother had been bred to a single F 1 or F 2 male.",
